# Ongoing Priorities

Regardless of development phase, HCP continues to prioritize:

* semantic interoperability;
* implementation independence;
* decentralized architecture;
* privacy by design;
* explainable correlation;
* human verification;
* backward compatibility whenever reasonably possible.

These principles remain stable throughout protocol evolution.

---

# Community Participation

HCP is developed as an open specification.

Contributions are encouraged through:

* issue reports;
* implementation feedback;
* interoperability testing;
* documentation improvements;
* reference implementations;
* protocol discussions.

Protocol evolution is driven by practical humanitarian needs rather than implementation-specific preferences.

---

# Roadmap Flexibility

This roadmap is informative.

Future phases may:

* change priorities;
* introduce new milestones;
* postpone planned work;
* incorporate community feedback.

Normative protocol behavior is defined exclusively by the HCP Specifications.

